# default.read-guard — shipped defaults for the read-guard hook.
#
# Flat list of path-prefix exclusions. The guard does not apply to a command
# that references any listed entry as a path token (preceded by a path-boundary
# char: whitespace, /, ', ", =, or start of line). Include the trailing slash
# to mean "this directory".
#
# Examples:
#   build/output/   # any path with /build/output/ in it
#   docs/dumps/     # arbitrary diagnostic dump directory
#
# Loaded together with $HOME/.claude/.read-guard and
# $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR/.read-guard — all three files concatenate. To remove a
# default rule, comment out the line here; there is no `!` negation.
#
# Note: the scratch root from the $CLAUDE_SCRATCH_ROOT env var (default
# ".scratch") is exempted automatically by the hook — do not list it here.
#
# Comments begin with # and run to end of line.
